    "graph": "All 24 tests pass and deliverables are written. Final summary:\n\nCracked the abbreviation SELECTION policy (BEHAVIOR.md §5c). The rule: a sub-term is abbreviated iff (1) its rendered length ≥ 10, (2) it occurs ≥ 2 times in the constraint system, and (3) it is not a tuple. Naming is bottom-up.\n\nThe key was recognizing the gate is rendered STRING LENGTH, not structural size or occurrence — which is why the prior investigator (measuring size + occurrence) couldn't explain sign(...) at 3 occ vs KDF(z) at 4 occ: sign(<...>,...) is ≥10 chars, KDF(z) is 6.\n\nNecessary-direction is corpus-exact: across all 97,538 legend entries in 11,564 graphs, min rendered length is exactly 10 (0 below), 0 are top-level tuples, and 0 abbreviated terms drawn ≥2× violate the length/tuple gates. Abbreviations with graph-occurrence 1 (e.g. SI3=sign(~y,k), drawn nowhere) confirm the occurrence universe is the whole system (graph nodes + the json sequent), recovered by mining the main/proof↔interactive-graph-def json/dot pairs.\n\nEach gate was independently confirmed by controlled live probes of the black-box server (crafted theories, --port= form): '12345678'(10 chars,×2) abbreviated but '1234567'(9,×2) not (boundary=10); a 42-char constant ×1 not abbreviated but a 12-char ×2 is (occ≥2 hard gate); an 18-char tuple ×2 not abbreviated while sibling h('longarg123') ×2 is, nesting to LO1='longarg123', H1='h(LO1)'.\n\nResidual (characterized, not byte-parity): for AC/DH sub-terms (^ * ⊕ ++ inv em hp pmult) tamarin counts occurrences over the solver's normalised term, so the same term is abbreviated in one proof state and not another (em(hp($A),hp($B)) inline in 56eeb42d, EM1 in 54eb2e2c) — 93% of exceptions; the rest are validation artifacts from expanding shared abbreviations before counting.\n\nImplemented as abbrev::select (MIN_ABBREV_LEN=10, MIN_ABBREV_OCC=2, tuple-excluded, bottom-up) with Term::render_len/is_tuple; 6 new tests reproduce each probe; full suite 24 tests incl. the 12,022-payload byte-exact roundtrip.\n\nDeliverables written: workspace/REPORT2.md, updated workspace/BEHAVIOR.md §5c/§6, workspace/QUERIES.log, graph-clean/src/{abbrev.rs,term.rs}, tests/abbrev_tests.rs. No tamarin-prover source was read; all claims trace to captured dot_corpus/manifests or live black-box probe output.",
    "web": "Done. All deliverables are in place, 38 tests pass, clippy clean, and the transient 620 MB extract is removed (regenerable in ~33 s via the jq loop documented in REPORT2.md).\n\nWhole-corpus HTML page generality: 15178/15178 captured `html` bodies reproduced byte-for-byte (100.00%) across all 81 manifests, via a new bulk harness that renders each body from my crate's templates.\nPer-family byte-parity: intdot/* 14705/14705 (100%, fully model-driven by render_intdot); overview/help 81/81 (100%); overview/proof/* 392/392 (100%) — the shell reproduced by render_page with west/center panes treated as opaque, exactly as the committed 3-page tests.\nThe html surface is exactly TWO families (no proof-method/source/diff html exists — those are JSON/text), so my templates already cover 100%; nothing was uncovered to extend.\nNon-circularity is enforced: the only value read back from an intdot target is the request-index the capture erased (keys normalized to `#`); the path-tail passthrough (0 tail-guard fails/14705) and title name (0 name-guard fails) are independently verified.\nOverview center pane tied to the already-100%-parity JSON envelope family: center == sibling main/* html + one trailing space — help 81/81 (load-timestamp masked), proof 309/392 exact; the 83 residuals are cross-version capture skew (main captured at v1, overview at v16), differing only in link indices + proof-state content (both prover fragments), never a template byte.\nSole remaining modeling gap: the west proof-script pane is generated (proofscript.rs) and byte-reproduced only for Chaum; for the other 70 theories it is an opaque per-(theory,version) fragment — the natural next round.\nNew artifacts: examples/corpus_html.rs (bulk harness); tests/fixtures/html_sample.ndjson + test html_page_generality_sample_byte_identical (20 bodies/6 theories/indices 1,3,8,16) locking generality into cargo test (37 → 38).\nAccess: derived only from oracle/captured_responses (jq/python) and prior live